The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 19 November is 104,903 (12,090.7 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 14 November, there were 4,731 new confirmed cases (545.3 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 07 November, there were 3,733 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 27% (998 extra cases).
